    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect PNF start response handling in VNF\n\n### Summary\nThe `vnf_nr_handle_pnf_start_response` function was invoking callbacks even when the PNF_START response contained error codes. This led to unexpected behavior in the VNF state machine where error responses were treated as successful completions.\n\nThis fix adds proper error code checking consistent with other NR response handlers.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf.c`: Added error code check before invoking `pnf_nr_start_resp` callback.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure VNF to handle PNF connections\n2. Send a PNF_START.response with error_code != 0\n3. Observe that the registered `pnf_nr_start_resp` callback is still invoked\n4. This causes incorrect state transitions in the VNF\n\nThe fix ensures that callbacks are only invoked when `msg.error_code == NFAPI_MSG_OK`, matching the behavior of other NR response handlers like `vnf_nr_handle_start_response`.\n"
}